What you need to know:

Sports Kenya chairman Fred Muteti said they were in a rush to fix the grass to ensure the field could host international matches, promising to complete the work in two weeksMuteti gave the clearest indication ever that President Uhuru Kenyatta would in February hand over the stadium to Meru County government, ordering contractors to spruce up the facilityImenti North deputy county commissioner Obel Ojwang said the stadium was 95 percent complete, assuring that the government was committed to completing it